      • addUniversity

        public static int addUniversity​(java.io.File csv)
                         throws java.io.IOException
        This method takes in a csv value, and goes through the file and takes each piece of data to use it to create a new university object. It adds each University object to the Universities ArrayList. If there are not enough values to fill a University object, then the method returns 1.
        Parameters:
        csv - A file object linking to a csv that will be parsed through for its contents
        Returns:
        0 if no errors, 1 if there is not enough values to create a new object
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException
        java.io.IOException
